WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.295 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.295 --> 00:00:07.670 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM HENRY:
It is considered

00:00:07.670 --> 00:00:11.500 align:middle line:84%
the most mysterious relic
of all human history,

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:14.460 align:middle line:84%
but is it a relic, or
is it something else?

00:00:14.460 --> 00:00:16.200 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE HENRY:
Next on "Arcanum:"

00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:18.780 align:middle line:84%
the secrets of the
Shroud of Turin.

00:00:18.780 --> 00:00:38.930 align:middle line:90%


00:00:38.930 --> 00:00:41.410 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: The Shroud of
Turin is a large, linen cloth

00:00:41.410 --> 00:00:45.300 align:middle line:84%
imbued with the image of
a tortured, crucified man.

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:47.690 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: The question of
whether the Shroud of Turin

00:00:47.690 --> 00:00:53.570 align:middle line:84%
in is the actual burial cloth
of Jesus is open, unanswered.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:55.320 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: Christian
belief says something

00:00:55.320 --> 00:00:57.920 align:middle line:84%
of extraordinary significance
happened in a tomb

00:00:57.920 --> 00:00:59.850 align:middle line:90%
just over 2000 years ago.

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:02.550 align:middle line:84%
This cloth was thought
to have been present.

00:01:02.550 --> 00:01:06.660 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: It is considered the
most important and most studied

00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:09.050 align:middle line:90%
relic of Christianity.

00:01:09.050 --> 00:01:10.930 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: In year 2000,
Cardinal Ratzinger,

00:01:10.930 --> 00:01:13.520 align:middle line:84%
later to be known as
Pope Benedict XVI,

00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:17.190 align:middle line:84%
wrote that the Shroud of Turin
is a truly mysterious image,

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.450 align:middle line:84%
which no human artistry
was capable of producing.

00:01:20.450 --> 00:01:24.570 align:middle line:84%
In some inexplicable way, it
appeared imprinted upon cloth

00:01:24.570 --> 00:01:27.560 align:middle line:84%
and believed to show
the true face of Christ,

00:01:27.560 --> 00:01:30.180 align:middle line:90%
the crucified and risen Lord.

00:01:30.180 --> 00:01:33.780 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: The shroud profoundly
challenges and confounds

00:01:33.780 --> 00:01:35.420 align:middle line:90%
human intellect.

00:01:35.420 --> 00:01:37.950 align:middle line:84%
Science has tried
to explain it, but

00:01:37.950 --> 00:01:42.880 align:middle line:84%
no universally accepted process
has being proposed to do so.

00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:47.950 align:middle line:84%
The image on the shroud defies
duplication by human hands.

00:01:47.950 --> 00:01:49.870 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAM: In June,
2008, three years

00:01:49.870 --> 00:01:52.230 align:middle line:10%
after he assumed the
papcy, Pope Benedict

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:55.040 align:middle line:10%
announced that the shroud
would be publicly displayed

00:01:55.040 --> 00:01:57.430 align:middle line:10%
in the spring of
2010, and stated

00:01:57.430 --> 00:01:59.520 align:middle line:10%
that he would like to go
to Turin to see it along

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:01.180 align:middle line:10%
with other pilgrims.

00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:03.870 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: During his visit
in Turin on Sunday, May

00:02:03.870 --> 00:02:09.639 align:middle line:84%
the second, 2010 Pope Benedict
described the Shroud of Turin

00:02:09.639 --> 00:02:15.740 align:middle line:84%
as an extraordinary icon--
the icon of holy Saturday,

00:02:15.740 --> 00:02:19.370 align:middle line:84%
corresponding in every way
to what the Gospels tell us

00:02:19.370 --> 00:02:24.500 align:middle line:84%
of Jesus-- an icon written
in blood, the blood of a man

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:28.810 align:middle line:84%
who was scourged, crowned
with thorns, crucified,

00:02:28.810 --> 00:02:31.870 align:middle line:84%
and whose right
side was pierced.

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:34.230 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: The pope said also
that in the Turin shroud,

00:02:34.230 --> 00:02:37.050 align:middle line:84%
we see as in a
mirror our suffering

00:02:37.050 --> 00:02:39.020 align:middle line:90%
in the suffering of Christ.

00:02:39.020 --> 00:02:42.590 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: Three years later,
on the 30th of March,

00:02:42.590 --> 00:02:46.090 align:middle line:84%
2013 as part of the
Easter celebrations,

00:02:46.090 --> 00:02:48.480 align:middle line:84%
there was an
extraordinary exposition

00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:51.800 align:middle line:84%
of the shroud in the
Cathedral of Turin.

00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:54.000 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAM: In a
carefully worded message,

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.510 align:middle line:10%
Pope Francis asked and answered
a rhetorical question--

00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.260 align:middle line:10%
how is it that the
faithful, like you, pause

00:03:00.260 --> 00:03:04.470 align:middle line:10%
before this icon of a man
scourged and crucified?

00:03:04.470 --> 00:03:06.270 align:middle line:84%
It is because the
man of the shroud

00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:09.900 align:middle line:84%
invites us to contemplate
Jesus of Nazareth.

00:03:09.900 --> 00:03:12.760 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: Pope Francis
recorded a video message

00:03:12.760 --> 00:03:14.890 align:middle line:84%
for the occasion, in
which he described

00:03:14.890 --> 00:03:20.680 align:middle line:84%
the image on the shroud
as this icon of a man,

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:24.190 align:middle line:84%
and stated the man
of the shroud invites

00:03:24.190 --> 00:03:28.099 align:middle line:84%
us to contemplate
Jesus of Nazareth.

00:03:28.099 --> 00:03:29.890 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: He continued
saying, "So looking

00:03:29.890 --> 00:03:34.000 align:middle line:84%
upon the man of the shroud, I
make Saint Francis of Assisi's

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:36.200 align:middle line:84%
prayer before the
crucifix my own.

00:03:36.200 --> 00:03:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Most high and glorious
God, enlighten the darkness

00:03:39.450 --> 00:03:42.740 align:middle line:84%
of my heart, and grant me
true faith, certain hope,

00:03:42.740 --> 00:03:45.130 align:middle line:84%
and perfect charity,
sense, and understanding,

00:03:45.130 --> 00:03:50.100 align:middle line:84%
Lord, so that I may carry out
your holy and true command."

00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:54.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: Pope Francis and his
predecessor Pope Benedict XVI

00:03:54.340 --> 00:03:59.050 align:middle line:84%
have both described the
Shroud of Turin as an icon.

00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:02.710 align:middle line:84%
In choosing this carefully
worded description,

00:04:02.710 --> 00:04:05.150 align:middle line:84%
we realize the
popes are telling us

00:04:05.150 --> 00:04:08.450 align:middle line:84%
something astounding
about the shroud.

00:04:08.450 --> 00:04:10.720 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: The Shroud
of Turin is not a relic.

00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:13.700 align:middle line:84%
It's an icon, and there's
a huge difference.

00:04:13.700 --> 00:04:17.300 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the shroud
may be the first icon.

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.269 align:middle line:84%
In our episode on
the transfiguration,

00:04:19.269 --> 00:04:21.680 align:middle line:90%
we decoded this term.

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:23.890 align:middle line:84%
>>CLARE: In William's
feature investigation,

00:04:23.890 --> 00:04:29.150 align:middle line:84%
he will help us gaze beyond the
surface of the Shroud of Turin,

00:04:29.150 --> 00:04:30.625 align:middle line:90%
the first icon.

00:04:30.625 --> 00:04:37.320 align:middle line:90%


00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.140 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAM: For millions of
Christians, the Shroud of Turin

00:04:40.140 --> 00:04:44.550 align:middle line:84%
is a symbol for the hope for the
afterlife and life after death.

00:04:44.550 --> 00:04:48.290 align:middle line:84%
But could it be more
than just a symbol?

00:04:48.290 --> 00:04:51.530 align:middle line:84%
Could it be an actual tool
that assists believers

00:04:51.530 --> 00:04:54.880 align:middle line:84%
in their journey
to resurrection?

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:58.240 align:middle line:84%
Is this why, in his carefully
worded message about the Shroud

00:04:58.240 --> 00:05:01.180 align:middle line:84%
of Turin, Pope Francis
asked and answered

00:05:01.180 --> 00:05:03.790 align:middle line:84%
that kind of odd
rhetorical question,

00:05:03.790 --> 00:05:07.060 align:middle line:84%
how is it that the
faithful, like you, pause

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:12.310 align:middle line:84%
before this icon of a man
scourged and crucified?

00:05:12.310 --> 00:05:14.380 align:middle line:84%
Is it because the
man of the shroud

00:05:14.380 --> 00:05:18.700 align:middle line:84%
invites us to contemplate
Jesus of Nazareth?

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:23.030 align:middle line:84%
In Christianity, an
icon is a sacred image

00:05:23.030 --> 00:05:27.210 align:middle line:84%
that is believed to be
charged with spiritual power.

00:05:27.210 --> 00:05:31.610 align:middle line:84%
They also believe it can
transmit this spiritual power.

00:05:31.610 --> 00:05:35.890 align:middle line:84%
In Christian art, an
icon is a living image

00:05:35.890 --> 00:05:41.010 align:middle line:84%
that functions as a
portal or a gateway.

00:05:41.010 --> 00:05:45.450 align:middle line:84%
It's literally considered to be
a two-way mirror, and a method

00:05:45.450 --> 00:05:49.580 align:middle line:84%
of communication with
the divine realms.

00:05:49.580 --> 00:05:54.000 align:middle line:84%
Icons were specially created
to enable a visceral encounter

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:59.810 align:middle line:84%
with a holy being, or to make
present a spiritual energy.

00:05:59.810 --> 00:06:02.230 align:middle line:84%
They are a form
of visual alchemy

00:06:02.230 --> 00:06:05.370 align:middle line:84%
that can help us in our
own transfiguration,

00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:07.360 align:middle line:90%
if that's our path.

00:06:07.360 --> 00:06:11.330 align:middle line:84%
They were specially created to
enable this visceral encounter

00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:14.420 align:middle line:84%
with a holy being, or to
make that spiritual energy

00:06:14.420 --> 00:06:17.650 align:middle line:90%
present in our bodies.

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:19.920 align:middle line:10%
Thus, they are
this visual alchemy

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:23.760 align:middle line:10%
that can assist us in
our transformation.

00:06:23.760 --> 00:06:27.140 align:middle line:84%
The amazing account
of the transformation,

00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:29.840 align:middle line:84%
or transfiguration of Jesus
from the book of Matthew

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:35.710 align:middle line:84%
says that after six days, Jesus
took with him Peter, James,

00:06:35.710 --> 00:06:38.660 align:middle line:84%
and John the brother of
James, and led them up

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:41.430 align:middle line:90%
a high mountain by themselves.

00:06:41.430 --> 00:06:46.180 align:middle line:84%
There, he was
transfigured before them.

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:50.700 align:middle line:84%
Jesus' face shone like
the Sun, and his clothes

00:06:50.700 --> 00:06:54.160 align:middle line:90%
became as white as light.

00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:58.900 align:middle line:84%
Just then, there appeared
before them Moses and Elijah,

00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:02.620 align:middle line:90%
talking with Jesus.

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:06.690 align:middle line:84%
For the icon makers of
the transfiguration icons,

00:07:06.690 --> 00:07:12.150 align:middle line:84%
these images became a
channel between two worlds.

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:16.880 align:middle line:10%
To an orthodox Christian, the
images are more than that.

00:07:16.880 --> 00:07:21.040 align:middle line:10%
They are a medium through which
the whole may be approached,

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:27.390 align:middle line:10%
and grace channeled,
like a two-way mirror.

00:07:27.390 --> 00:07:31.930 align:middle line:84%
In the magical alchemical
imagination of the icon makers,

00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:38.670 align:middle line:84%
these images were designed to be
actual doors to another world.

00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:43.320 align:middle line:84%
Our world and the spiritual
world are open to each other

00:07:43.320 --> 00:07:44.660 align:middle line:90%
through the icon.

00:07:44.660 --> 00:07:46.220 align:middle line:84%
And this is why
it's so important

00:07:46.220 --> 00:07:47.940 align:middle line:84%
to make the distinction
in the Pope's

00:07:47.940 --> 00:07:51.040 align:middle line:84%
terminology between the
shroud being a relic

00:07:51.040 --> 00:07:54.410 align:middle line:90%
and the shroud being an icon.

00:07:54.410 --> 00:07:58.680 align:middle line:84%
The icon makers held that
through prayer and meditation,

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:02.490 align:middle line:84%
believers could actually come
to perceive the same divine

00:08:02.490 --> 00:08:08.300 align:middle line:84%
light that shone around Jesus
during his transfiguration.

00:08:08.300 --> 00:08:13.410 align:middle line:84%
Through contemplation,
meditation, and reflection

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:18.820 align:middle line:84%
on the icon, we begin to
reflect the light experienced

00:08:18.820 --> 00:08:22.470 align:middle line:90%
by Jesus in our lives.

00:08:22.470 --> 00:08:26.750 align:middle line:84%
By mirroring Christ, the
transfiguration icon makers

00:08:26.750 --> 00:08:31.660 align:middle line:84%
proposed, we can put on
our own cloak of light,

00:08:31.660 --> 00:08:35.120 align:middle line:84%
our garment of light, our robe
of light, or shining garment,

00:08:35.120 --> 00:08:38.830 align:middle line:90%
as the light body is called.

00:08:38.830 --> 00:08:41.230 align:middle line:84%
In addition to calling
the Shroud of Turin

00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:45.340 align:middle line:84%
an icon-- again, not
a relic-- Pope Francis

00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:50.260 align:middle line:84%
said that in the shroud,
we see as in a mirror

00:08:50.260 --> 00:08:53.810 align:middle line:84%
our suffering in the
suffering of Christ.

00:08:53.810 --> 00:08:56.830 align:middle line:84%
Francis is clearly
speaking the language

00:08:56.830 --> 00:08:59.620 align:middle line:84%
of the icon makers,
the language of those

00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:02.820 align:middle line:84%
who know the secrets
of this visual alchemy.

00:09:02.820 --> 00:09:05.440 align:middle line:84%
And he's one step
away from telling us

00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:09.510 align:middle line:84%
that we can actually use the
Shroud of Turin as a mirror

00:09:09.510 --> 00:09:13.360 align:middle line:84%
in order to assist us in
our own transfiguration.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:16.830 align:middle line:84%
This is more than
poetic language.

00:09:16.830 --> 00:09:19.470 align:middle line:84%
The Pope, Francis,
is telling us,

00:09:19.470 --> 00:09:23.830 align:middle line:84%
in my view, that the shroud
is in fact a two-way mirror

00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:26.710 align:middle line:84%
and a method of communication
with the divine realm,

00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:30.750 align:middle line:84%
specifically with
the light of Christ.

00:09:30.750 --> 00:09:37.350 align:middle line:84%
So is this icon literally,
literally a portal or conduit

00:09:37.350 --> 00:09:39.110 align:middle line:90%
to another world?

00:09:39.110 --> 00:09:43.540 align:middle line:84%
Did Jesus leave this as
a message of healing?

00:09:43.540 --> 00:09:47.880 align:middle line:84%
Did he leave this icon as
a way to connect with him,

00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:51.060 align:middle line:84%
to open a portal to
the divine realm?

00:09:51.060 --> 00:09:54.320 align:middle line:84%
Is the material world
and the spiritual world

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:59.570 align:middle line:84%
open to each other through the
Christ icon or the shroud icon?

00:09:59.570 --> 00:10:04.370 align:middle line:84%
Just how far can
we stretch this?

00:10:04.370 --> 00:10:07.595 align:middle line:84%
In his book "The Sign,"
British art historian Thomas de

00:10:07.595 --> 00:10:11.620 align:middle line:84%
Wesselow has proposed a theory
that the shroud contains

00:10:11.620 --> 00:10:14.830 align:middle line:84%
the living light of
Christ, literally.

00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:17.500 align:middle line:84%
He says that this
light was captured

00:10:17.500 --> 00:10:19.940 align:middle line:90%
by the material of the shroud.

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:22.620 align:middle line:84%
In fact, he cites
a Chinese ceremony

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:26.560 align:middle line:84%
which involved enticing
into a sick man's coat

00:10:26.560 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
the departing spirit, which
has already left his body.

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:36.380 align:middle line:84%
Wesselow proposes that when Mary
Magdalene saw the resurrected

00:10:36.380 --> 00:10:40.510 align:middle line:84%
Jesus on Easter morning,
that what she actually saw

00:10:40.510 --> 00:10:47.520 align:middle line:84%
was the Shroud of Turin with the
man of light imprinted upon it.

00:10:47.520 --> 00:10:49.820 align:middle line:84%
Analogously, the
shroud could have

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:52.720 align:middle line:84%
been seen as a coat,
de Wesselow notes,

00:10:52.720 --> 00:10:56.420 align:middle line:84%
in which Jesus' spirit
has been caught.

00:10:56.420 --> 00:11:00.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is very interesting,
because this view is in harmony

00:11:00.700 --> 00:11:04.670 align:middle line:84%
with the view expressed in
several episodes of "Arcanum."

00:11:04.670 --> 00:11:07.660 align:middle line:84%
That is, the ancient
purveyors of arcanum

00:11:07.660 --> 00:11:11.080 align:middle line:84%
utilized the symbol
of a robe or coat

00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:15.110 align:middle line:84%
as a metaphor for the craft
of human transformation

00:11:15.110 --> 00:11:17.040 align:middle line:90%
into light.

00:11:17.040 --> 00:11:19.670 align:middle line:10%
In our episode on
ascension thrones,

00:11:19.670 --> 00:11:22.840 align:middle line:10%
we noted that Elias, the
messiah's forerunner,

00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:25.810 align:middle line:10%
is a man to whom many great
mysteries are attached,

00:11:25.810 --> 00:11:30.260 align:middle line:10%
especially those concerning
a transmittable cloak, coat,

00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:32.290 align:middle line:10%
or garment.

00:11:32.290 --> 00:11:36.100 align:middle line:10%
According to the Book of
Kings, he raised the dead,

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:38.020 align:middle line:10%
brought fire down
from the sky, and was

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:40.740 align:middle line:10%
taken up in a whirlwind,
either accompanied

00:11:40.740 --> 00:11:45.410 align:middle line:10%
by a chariot of horses of flame,
or riding in this chariot.

00:11:45.410 --> 00:11:50.150 align:middle line:84%
And it is clear that Elijah
knew the secret of arcanum.

00:11:50.150 --> 00:11:52.880 align:middle line:84%
Elijah possessed
ancient keys that

00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:56.020 align:middle line:84%
allowed him to be
transported from one location

00:11:56.020 --> 00:11:58.680 align:middle line:84%
to another, to raise the
dead, to command rain,

00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:02.250 align:middle line:84%
and even to baffle
world leaders.

00:12:02.250 --> 00:12:07.550 align:middle line:84%
Importantly, as Elijah ascended
in his Merkaba whirlwind,

00:12:07.550 --> 00:12:12.790 align:middle line:84%
he did so in a form other than
as a flesh and blood human.

00:12:12.790 --> 00:12:16.340 align:middle line:84%
He appears to have
adopted a body that

00:12:16.340 --> 00:12:21.260 align:middle line:84%
could bend space
and time, and also

00:12:21.260 --> 00:12:25.040 align:middle line:84%
to dematerialize
and rematerialize

00:12:25.040 --> 00:12:27.910 align:middle line:84%
at another location
or frequency.

00:12:27.910 --> 00:12:30.900 align:middle line:84%
This teaching is also found
in the Tibetan rainbow body

00:12:30.900 --> 00:12:32.920 align:middle line:90%
tradition.

00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:36.740 align:middle line:84%
This special ability
is transmittable

00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:41.510 align:middle line:84%
and is symbolized by Elijah's
pala garment, or power garment,

00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:45.120 align:middle line:84%
which he transmitted
to his priest Elisha

00:12:45.120 --> 00:12:48.830 align:middle line:90%
as he rose into the heavens.

00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:52.540 align:middle line:84%
In Christian tradition,
Elijah reincarnated

00:12:52.540 --> 00:12:54.920 align:middle line:90%
as John the Baptist.

