00:24:58.790 --> 00:25:00.410 align:middle line:90%
They're perfect.

00:25:00.410 --> 00:25:04.860 align:middle line:84%
This means the body was
levitating, hovering,

00:25:04.860 --> 00:25:09.060 align:middle line:84%
or floating between the
two sides of the Shroud.

00:25:09.060 --> 00:25:11.420 align:middle line:84%
As Piczek says,
this means there's

00:25:11.420 --> 00:25:14.070 align:middle line:90%
no gravity involved here.

00:25:14.070 --> 00:25:17.010 align:middle line:84%
In addition, Piczek
observed that the image

00:25:17.010 --> 00:25:19.550 align:middle line:90%
is distortion free.

00:25:19.550 --> 00:25:23.020 align:middle line:84%
This is impossible if the
shroud was wrapped, draped,

00:25:23.020 --> 00:25:25.110 align:middle line:90%
or otherwise placed on the body.

00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:29.880 align:middle line:84%
It is only possible if the
shroud was absolutely taut,

00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:34.410 align:middle line:84%
stretched like a paint
canvas on a frame.

00:25:34.410 --> 00:25:38.770 align:middle line:84%
Piczek's work strongly suggests
that the image of Jesus

00:25:38.770 --> 00:25:43.960 align:middle line:84%
